class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>1</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> (coming from the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Greek">/wiki/Ancient_Greek</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ancient Greek</a>"&gt;</span><span>Ancient Greek</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ancient Greek (to 1453)-language text</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">lang</span>="<a class="attribute-value">grc</a>"&gt;</span><span>ἀνούρα</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>, literally 'without tail'). The oldest fossil "proto-frog" </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triadobatrachus">/wiki/Triadobatrachus</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Triadobatrachus</a>"&gt;</span><span>Triadobatrachus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> is known from the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Early_Triassic">/wiki/Early_Triassic</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Early Triassic</a>"&gt;</span><span>Early Triassic</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madagascar">/wiki/Madagascar</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Madagascar</a>"&gt;</span><span>Madagascar</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (250</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">nowrap</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#160;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myr">/wiki/Myr</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Myr</a>"&gt;</span><span>million years ago</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>), but </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecular_clock">/wiki/Molecular_clock</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Molecular clock</a>"&gt;</span><span>molecular clock dating</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> suggests their split from other amphibians may extend further back to the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permian">/wiki/Permian</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Permian</a>"&gt;</span><span>Permian</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, 265</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">nowrap</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#160;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>million years ago. Frogs are widely distributed, ranging from the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropics">/wiki/Tropics</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tropics</a>"&gt;</span><span>tropics</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> to </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Subarctic">/wiki/Subarctic</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Subarctic</a>"&gt;</span><span>subarctic</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> regions, but the greatest concentration of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Species_diversity">/wiki/Species_diversity</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Species diversity</a>"&gt;</span><span>species diversity</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> is in </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_rainforest">/wiki/Tropical_rainforest</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tropical rainforest</a>"&gt;</span><span>tropical rainforest</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. Frogs account for around 88% of extant amphibian species. They are also one of the five most diverse </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebrate">/wiki/Vertebrate</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Vertebrate</a>"&gt;</span><span>vertebrate</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> orders. Warty frog species tend to be called </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toad">/wiki/Toad</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Toad</a>"&gt;</span><span>toads</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, but the distinction between frogs and toads is informal, not from </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Taxonomy_(biology)">/wiki/Taxonomy_(biology)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Taxonomy (biology)</a>"&gt;</span><span>taxonomy</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> or evolutionary history.
</span></span><span id="line1323"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>An adult frog has a stout body, protruding </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Eye">/wiki/Eye</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Eye</a>"&gt;</span><span>eyes</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, anteriorly-attached </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tongue">/wiki/Tongue</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tongue</a>"&gt;</span><span>tongue</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, limbs folded underneath, and no </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tail">/wiki/Tail</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tail</a>"&gt;</span><span>tail</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (the tail of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tailed_frog">/wiki/Tailed_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tailed frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>tailed frogs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> is an extension of the male cloaca). Frogs have </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gland">/wiki/Gland</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Gland</a>"&gt;</span><span>glandular</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> skin, with secretions ranging from distasteful to toxic. Their skin varies in colour from well-</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Camouflage">/wiki/Camouflage</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Camouflage</a>"&gt;</span><span>camouflaged</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> dappled brown, grey and green to vivid patterns of bright red or yellow and black to show toxicity and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aposematism">/wiki/Aposematism</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Aposematism</a>"&gt;</span><span>ward off predators</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. Adult frogs live in fresh water and on dry land; some species are adapted for living underground or in trees.
</span></span><span id="line1324"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Frogs typically lay their </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Egg">/wiki/Egg</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Egg</a>"&gt;</span><span>eggs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> in the water. The eggs hatch into aquatic </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Larva">/wiki/Larva</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Larva</a>"&gt;</span><span>larvae</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> called </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tadpole">/wiki/Tadpole</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tadpole</a>"&gt;</span><span>tadpoles</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> that have tails and internal </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gill">/wiki/Gill</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Gill</a>"&gt;</span><span>gills</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. They have highly specialised rasping mouth parts suitable for </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Herbivore">/wiki/Herbivore</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Herbivore</a>"&gt;</span><span>herbivorous</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Omnivore">/wiki/Omnivore</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Omnivore</a>"&gt;</span><span>omnivorous</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> or </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planktivore">/wiki/Planktivore</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Planktivore</a>"&gt;</span><span>planktivorous</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> diets. The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biological_life_cycle">/wiki/Biological_life_cycle</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Biological life cycle</a>"&gt;</span><span>life cycle</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> is completed when they </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metamorphosis">/wiki/Metamorphosis</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Metamorphosis</a>"&gt;</span><span>metamorphose</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> into adults. A few species deposit eggs on land or bypass the tadpole stage. Adult frogs generally have a carnivorous diet consisting of small </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invertebrates">/wiki/Invertebrates</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Invertebrates</a>"&gt;</span><span>invertebrates</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, but omnivorous species exist and a few feed on plant matter. Frog skin has a rich </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_flora">/wiki/Skin_flora</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Skin flora</a>"&gt;</span><span>microbiome</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> which is important to their health. Frogs are extremely efficient at converting what they eat into body mass. They are an important food source for </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Predation">/wiki/Predation</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Predation</a>"&gt;</span><span>predators</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and part of the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Food_web">/wiki/Food_web</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Food web</a>"&gt;</span><span>food web</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> dynamics of many of the world's </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ecosystem">/wiki/Ecosystem</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ecosystem</a>"&gt;</span><span>ecosystems</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. The skin is </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Semi-permeable">/wiki/Semi-permeable</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Semi-permeable</a>"&gt;</span><span>semi-permeable</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, making them susceptible to dehydration, so they either live in moist places or have special adaptations to deal with dry habitats. Frogs produce a wide range of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Animal_communication">/wiki/Animal_communication</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Animal communication</a>"&gt;</span><span>vocalisations</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, particularly in their </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breeding_season">/wiki/Breeding_season</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Breeding season</a>"&gt;</span><span>breeding season</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, and exhibit many different kinds of complex </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ethology">/wiki/Ethology</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ethology</a>"&gt;</span><span>behaviors</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> to attract mates, to fend off predators and to generally survive.
</span></span><span id="line1325"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Frogs are valued as food by humans and also have many cultural roles in literature, symbolism and religion. They are also seen as </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bioindicator">/wiki/Bioindicator</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bioindicator</a>"&gt;</span><span>environmental bellwethers</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, with declines in frog populations often viewed as early warning signs of environmental damage. Frog populations have declined significantly since the 1950s. More than one third of species are considered to be </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Threatened_species">/wiki/Threatened_species</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Threatened species</a>"&gt;</span><span>threatened</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> with </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extinct">/wiki/Extinct</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Extinct</a>"&gt;</span><span>extinction</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and over 120 are believed to have become extinct since the 1980s. The number of malformations among frogs is on the rise and an emerging </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fungus">/wiki/Fungus</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Fungus</a>"&gt;</span><span>fungal</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> disease, </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chytridiomycosis">/wiki/Chytridiomycosis</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Chytridiomycosis</a>"&gt;</span><span>chytridiomycosis</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, has spread around the world. </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Conservation_biology">/wiki/Conservation_biology</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Conservation biology</a>"&gt;</span><span>Conservation biologists</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> are working to understand the causes of these problems and to resolve them.
</span></span><span id="line1326"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1327"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">meta</span> <span class="attribute-name">property</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw:PageProp/toc</a>" <span>/</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1328"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">div</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-heading mw-heading2</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">h2</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Etymology_and_taxonomy</a>"&gt;</span><span>Etymology and taxonomy</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">h2</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">div</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1329"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>The use of the common names </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Toad">/wiki/Toad</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Toad</a>"&gt;</span><span>toad</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> has no taxonomic justification. From a classification perspective, all members of the order Anura are frogs, but only members of the family </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bufonidae">/wiki/Bufonidae</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bufonidae</a>"&gt;</span><span>Bufonidae</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> are considered "true toads". </span></span><span id="line1344"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Frogs and toads are broadly classified into three suborders: </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archaeobatrachia">/wiki/Archaeobatrachia</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Archaeobatrachia</a>"&gt;</span><span>Archaeobatrachia</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, which includes four families of primitive frogs; </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesobatrachia">/wiki/Mesobatrachia</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Mesobatrachia</a>"&gt;</span><span>Mesobatrachia</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, which includes five families of more evolutionary intermediate frogs; and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neobatrachia">/wiki/Neobatrachia</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Neobatrachia</a>"&gt;</span><span>Neobatrachia</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, by far the largest group, which contains the remaining families of modern frogs, including most common species throughout the world. The suborder Neobatrachia is further divided into the two superfamilies </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyloidea">/wiki/Hyloidea</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Hyloidea</a>"&gt;</span><span>Hyloidea</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ranoidea">/wiki/Ranoidea</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ranoidea</a>"&gt;</span><span>Ranoidea</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-20</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-20">#cite_note-20</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>20</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> This classification is based on such </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morphology_(biology)">/wiki/Morphology_(biology)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Morphology (biology)</a>"&gt;</span><span>morphological</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> features as the number of vertebrae, the structure of the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pectoral_girdle">/wiki/Pectoral_girdle</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Pectoral girdle</a>"&gt;</span><span>pectoral girdle</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, and the morphology of tadpoles. While this classification is largely accepted, relationships among families of frogs are still debated.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-21</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-21">#cite_note-21</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>21</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1345"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Some species of anurans </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_(biology)">/wiki/Hybrid_(biology)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Hybrid (biology)</a>"&gt;</span><span>hybridise</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> readily. For instance, the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Pelophylax esculentus</span><span>&lt;/<span frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>P. lessonae</span><span>&lt;/<span frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>P. ridibundus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>).</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-22</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>22</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yellow-bellied_toad">/wiki/Yellow-bellied_toad</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Yellow-bellied toad</a>"&gt;</span><span>B. variegata</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> are similar in forming hybrids. These are less fertile than their parents, giving rise to a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hybrid_zone">/wiki/Hybrid_zone</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Hybrid zone</a>"&gt;</span><span>hybrid zone</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> where the hybrids are prevalent.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-23</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-23">#cite_note-23</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>23</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1346"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1347"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">div</span> <span class="attribute-name">style</span>="<a class="attribute-value">clear:left;</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value"></a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">div</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1348"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">div</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-heading mw-heading2</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">h2</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Evolution</a>"&gt;</span><span>Evolution</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">h2</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">div</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1349"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>The origins and evolutionary relationships between the three main groups of amphibians are hotly debated. A </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Molecular_phylogeny">/wiki/Molecular_phylogeny</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Molecular phylogeny</a>"&gt;</span><span>molecular phylogeny</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> based on </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ribosomal_DNA">/wiki/Ribosomal_DNA</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ribosomal DNA</a>"&gt;</span><span>rDNA</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> analysis dating from 2005 suggests that </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salamanders">/wiki/Salamanders</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Salamanders</a>"&gt;</span><span>salamanders</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caecilian">/wiki/Caecilian</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Caecilian</a>"&gt;</span><span>caecilians</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> are more closely related to each other than they are to frogs and the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Genetic_divergence">/wiki/Genetic_divergence</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Genetic divergence</a>"&gt;</span><span>divergence</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> of the three groups took place in the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Paleozoic">/wiki/Paleozoic</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Paleozoic</a>"&gt;</span><span>Paleozoic</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> or early </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesozoic">/wiki/Mesozoic</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Mesozoic</a>"&gt;</span><span>Mesozoic</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> before the break-up of the supercontinent </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pangaea">/wiki/Pangaea</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Pangaea</a>"&gt;</span><span>Pangaea</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and soon after their divergence from the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sarcopterygii">/wiki/Sarcopterygii</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Sarcopterygii</a>"&gt;</span><span>lobe-finned fishes</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. This would help account for the relative scarcity of amphibian fossils from the period before the groups split.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-24</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-24">#cite_note-24</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>24</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Another molecular phylogenetic analysis conducted about the same time concluded that </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lissamphibian">/wiki/Lissamphibian</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Lissamphibian</a>"&gt;</span><span>lissamphibians</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> first appeared about 330 million years ago and that the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temnospondyli">/wiki/Temnospondyli</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Temnospondyli</a>"&gt;</span><span>temnospondyl-origin</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> hypothesis is more credible than other theories. The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Neobatrachia">/wiki/Neobatrachia</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Neobatrachia</a>"&gt;</span><span>neobatrachians</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> seemed to have originated in Africa/India, the salamanders in East Asia and the caecilians in tropical Pangaea.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-25</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-25">#cite_note-25</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>25</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Other researchers, while agreeing with the main thrust of this study, questioned the choice of calibration points used to synchronise the data. They proposed that the date of lissamphibian diversification should be placed in the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Permian">/wiki/Permian</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Permian</a>"&gt;</span><span>Permian</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, rather less than 300 million years ago, a date in better agreement with the palaeontological data.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-26</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-26">#cite_note-26</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>26</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> A further study in 2011 using both extinct and living taxa sampled for morphological, as well as molecular data, came to the conclusion that Lissamphibia is </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Monophyly">/wiki/Monophyly</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Monophyly</a>"&gt;</span><span>monophyletic</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and that it should be nested within </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lepospondyli">/wiki/Lepospondyli</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Lepospondyli</a>"&gt;</span><span>Lepospondyli</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> rather than within </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temnospondyli">/wiki/Temnospondyli</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Temnospondyli</a>"&gt;</span><span>Temnospondyli</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. The study postulated that Lissamphibia originated no earlier than the late </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carboniferous">/wiki/Carboniferous</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Carboniferous</a>"&gt;</span><span>Carboniferous</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, some 290 to 305 million years ago. The split between Anura and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Caudata">/wiki/Caudata</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Caudata</a>"&gt;</span><span>Caudata</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> was estimated as taking place 292 million years ago, rather later than most molecular studies suggest, with the caecilians splitting off 239 million years ago.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-27</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-27">#cite_note-27</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>27</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1350"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>

</span></span><span id="line1352"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>In 2008, </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gerobatrachus_hottoni">/wiki/Gerobatrachus_hottoni</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Gerobatrachus hottoni</a>"&gt;</span><span>Gerobatrachus hottoni</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>, a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Temnospondyli">/wiki/Temnospondyli</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Temnospondyli</a>"&gt;</span><span>temnospondyl</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> with many frog- and salamander-like characteristics, was discovered in </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Texas">/wiki/Texas</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Texas</a>"&gt;</span><span>Texas</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. It dated back 290 million years and was hailed as a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" fossil</a>"&gt;</span><span>missing link</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span salamanders, consistent with the widely accepted hypothesis that frogs and salamanders are more closely related to each other (forming a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-28</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dissorophoidea">/wiki/Dissorophoidea</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a amphibians.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-M<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-M&amp;L09-30">#cite_note-M<span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line1353"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Salientia">/wiki/Salientia</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Salientia</a>"&gt;</span><span>Salientia</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (Latin </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>salire</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>salio</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>), "to jump") is the name of the total group that includes modern frogs in the order Anura as well as their close fossil relatives, the "proto-frogs" or "stem-frogs". The common features possessed by these proto-frogs include 14 </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebral_column">/wiki/Vertebral_column</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Vertebral column</a>"&gt;</span><span>presacral vertebrae</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (modern frogs have eight or 9), a long and forward-sloping </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ilium_(bone)">/wiki/Ilium_(bone)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ilium (bone)</a>"&gt;</span><span>ilium</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> in the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pelvis">/wiki/Pelvis</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Pelvis</a>"&gt;</span><span>pelvis</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, the presence of a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parietal_bone">/wiki/Parietal_bone</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Parietal bone</a>"&gt;</span><span>frontoparietal bone</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, and a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mandible">/wiki/Mandible</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Mandible</a>"&gt;</span><span>lower jaw</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> without teeth. The earliest known amphibians that were more closely related to frogs than to salamanders are </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triadobatrachus_massinoti">/wiki/Triadobatrachus_massinoti</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Triadobatrachus massinoti</a>"&gt;</span><span>Triadobatrachus massinoti</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>, from the early </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Triassic">/wiki/Triassic</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Triassic</a>"&gt;</span><span>Triassic</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> period of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madagascar">/wiki/Madagascar</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Madagascar</a>"&gt;</span><span>Madagascar</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (about 250 million years ago), and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Czatkobatrachus_polonicus">/wiki/Czatkobatrachus_polonicus</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Czatkobatrachus polonicus</a>"&gt;</span><span>Czatkobatrachus polonicus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poland">/wiki/Poland</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Triadobatrachus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>).</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-TOLweb_31-0</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-TOLweb-31">#cite_note-TOLweb-31</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>31</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> The skull of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Triadobatrachus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> is frog-like, being broad with large eye sockets, but the fossil has features diverging from modern frogs. These include a longer body with more </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vertebrae">/wiki/Vertebrae</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Vertebrae</a>"&gt;</span><span>vertebrae</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. The tail has separate vertebrae unlike the fused urostyle or coccyx in modern frogs. The tibia and fibula bones are also separate, making it probable that </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Triadobatrachus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> was not an efficient leaper.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-TOLweb_31-1</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-TOLweb-31">#cite_note-TOLweb-31</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>31</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="attribute-value">cite_ref-51</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>51</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> but the smallest species often have hands and feet where some of the digits are vestigial.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-52</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-52">#cite_note-52</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>52</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Frogs must be able to move quickly through their environment to catch prey and escape predators, and numerous adaptations help them to do so. Most frogs are either proficient at jumping or are descended from ancestors that were, with much of the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Musculoskeletal">/wiki/Musculoskeletal</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Musculoskeletal</a>"&gt;</span><span>musculoskeletal</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morphology_(biology)">/wiki/Morphology_(biology)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Morphology (biology)</a>"&gt;</span><span>morphology</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> modified for this purpose. The tibia, fibula, and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tarsus_(skeleton)">/wiki/Tarsus_(skeleton)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Tarsus (skeleton)</a>"&gt;</span><span>tarsals</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> have been fused into a single strong </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bone">/wiki/Bone</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bone</a>"&gt;</span><span>bone</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, as have the radius and ulna in the fore limbs (which must absorb the impact on landing). The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Metatarsals">/wiki/Metatarsals</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Metatarsals</a>"&gt;</span><span>metatarsals</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> have become elongated to add to the leg length and allow frogs to push against the ground for a longer period on take-off. The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ilium_(bone)">/wiki/Ilium_(bone)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ilium (bone)</a>"&gt;</span><span>ilium</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> has elongated and formed a mobile joint with the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sacrum">/wiki/Sacrum</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Sacrum</a>"&gt;</span><span>sacrum</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> which, in specialist jumpers such as ranids and hylids, functions as an additional limb joint to further power the leaps. The tail vertebrae have fused into a urostyle which is retracted inside the pelvis. This enables the force to be transferred from the legs to the body during a leap.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Flam_47-1</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-Flam-47">#cite_note-Flam-47</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>47</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2641"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>
