href="view-source:https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg/220px-Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg">//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg/220px-Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg</a>" <span class="attribute-name">decoding</span>="<a class="attribute-value">async</a>" <span class="attribute-name">width</span>="<a class="attribute-value">220</a>" <span class="attribute-name">height</span>="<a class="attribute-value">156</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-file-element</a>" <span class="attribute-name">srcset</span>="<a class="attribute-value">//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg/330px-Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/ab/Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg/440px-Dendrobates_pumilio.jpg 2x</a>" <span class="attribute-name">data-file-width</span>="<a class="attribute-value">1000</a>" <span class="attribute-name">data-file-height</span>="<a class="attribute-value">709</a>" <span>/</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">figcaption</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Strawberry_poison-dart_frog">/wiki/Strawberry_poison-dart_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Strawberry poison-dart frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>Strawberry poison-dart frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> contains numerous alkaloids which deter predators.</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">figcaption</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">figure</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2799"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>At first sight, frogs seem rather defenceless because of their small size, slow movement, thin skin, and lack of defensive structures, such as spines, claws or teeth. Many use camouflage to avoid detection, the skin often being spotted or streaked in neutral colours that allow a stationary frog to merge into its surroundings. Some can make prodigious leaps, often into water, that help them to evade potential attackers, while many have other defensive adaptations and strategies.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Stebbins_130-4</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-Stebbins-130">#cite_note-Stebbins-130</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>130</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2800"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>The skin of many frogs contains mild toxic substances called </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bufotoxin">/wiki/Bufotoxin</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bufotoxin</a>"&gt;</span><span>bufotoxins</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> to make them unpalatable to potential predators. Most toads and some frogs have large poison glands, the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Parotoid_gland">/wiki/Parotoid_gland</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Parotoid gland</a>"&gt;</span><span>parotoid glands</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, located on the sides of their heads behind the eyes and other glands elsewhere on their bodies. These glands secrete mucus and a range of toxins that make frogs slippery to hold and distasteful or poisonous. If the noxious effect is immediate, the predator may cease its action and the frog may escape. If the effect develops more slowly, the predator may learn to avoid that species in future.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-186</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-186">#cite_note-186</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>186</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Poisonous frogs tend to advertise their toxicity with bright colours, an adaptive strategy known as </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aposematism">/wiki/Aposematism</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Aposematism</a>"&gt;</span><span>aposematism</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poison_dart_frog">/wiki/Poison_dart_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Poison dart frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>poison dart frogs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> in the family Dendrobatidae do this. They are typically red, orange, or yellow, often with contrasting black markings on their bodies. </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Allobates_zaparo">/wiki/Allobates_zaparo</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Allobates zaparo</a>"&gt;</span><span>Allobates zaparo</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> is not poisonous, but mimics the appearance of two different toxic species with which it shares a common range in an effort to deceive predators.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-187</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-187">#cite_note-187</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>187</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>  Other species, such as the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/European_Fire-bellied_Toad">/wiki/European_Fire-bellied_Toad</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">European Fire-bellied Toad</a>"&gt;</span><span>European fire-bellied toad</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Bombina bombina</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>), have their warning colour underneath. They "flash" this when attacked, adopting a pose that exposes the vivid colouring on their bellies.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Bb_4-1</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-Bb-4">#cite_note-Bb-4</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>4</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>

</span></span><span id="line2803"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Some frogs, such as the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poison_dart_frog">/wiki/Poison_dart_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Poison dart frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>poison dart frogs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, are especially toxic. The native peoples of South America extract poison from these frogs to apply to their </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dart_(missile)">/wiki/Dart_(missile)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Dart (missile)</a>"&gt;</span><span>weapons</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> for hunting,</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-188</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-188">#cite_note-188</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>188</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> although few species are toxic enough to be used for this purpose. themselves.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-192</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a Many predators of frogs have become adapted to tolerate high levels of these poisons, but other creatures, including humans who handle the frogs, may be severely affected.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-193</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-193">#cite_note-193</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>193</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2804"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Some frogs use bluff or deception. The European common toad (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Bufo bufo</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) adopts a characteristic stance when attacked, inflating its body and standing with its hindquarters raised and its head lowered.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-194</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-194">#cite_note-194</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>194</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> The bullfrog (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Rana catesbeiana</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) crouches down with eyes closed and head tipped forward when threatened. This places the parotoid glands in the most effective position, the other glands on its back begin to ooze noxious secretions and the most vulnerable parts of its body are protected.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Stebbins_130-5</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-Stebbins-130">#cite_note-Stebbins-130</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>130</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Another tactic used by some frogs is to "scream", the sudden loud noise tending to startle the predator. The grey tree frog (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hyla_versicolor">/wiki/Hyla_versicolor</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Hyla versicolor</a>"&gt;</span><span>Hyla versicolor</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) makes an explosive sound that sometimes repels the shrew </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blarina_brevicauda">/wiki/Blarina_brevicauda</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Blarina brevicauda</a>"&gt;</span><span>Blarina brevicauda</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Stebbins_130-6</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Although toads are avoided by many predators, the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Common_Garter_Snake">/wiki/Common_Garter_Snake</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Common Garter Snake</a>"&gt;</span><span>common garter snake</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Thamnophis sirtalis</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) regularly feeds on them. The strategy employed by juvenile American toads (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bufo_americanus">/wiki/Bufo_americanus</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bufo americanus</a>"&gt;</span><span>Bufo americanus</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) on being approached by a snake is to crouch down and remain immobile. This is usually successful, with the snake passing by and the toad remaining undetected. If it is encountered by the snake's head, however, the toad hops away before crouching defensively.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-195</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-195">#cite_note-195</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>195</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2805"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>

<span>/</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">figcaption</span>&gt;</span><span>Although frogs are most </span></span><span id="line2808"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Frogs live on every continent except Antarctica, but they are not present on certain islands, especially those far away from continental land masses.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-196</a>" <span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Many species are isolated in restricted ranges by changes of climate or inhospitable territory, such as stretches of sea, mountain ridges, deserts, forest clearance, road construction, or other human-made barriers.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-198</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Usually, a greater diversity of frogs occurs in tropical areas than in temperate regions, such as Europe.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-199</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Some frogs inhabit arid areas, such as deserts, and rely on specific adaptations to survive. Members of the Australian genus </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cyclorana">/wiki/Cyclorana</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Cyclorana</a>"&gt;</span><span>Cyclorana</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span> bury themselves underground where they create a water-impervious cocoon in which to </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aestivation">/wiki/Aestivation</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Aestivation</a>"&gt;</span><span>aestivate</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> during dry periods. Once it rains, they emerge, find a temporary pool, and breed. Egg and tadpole development is very fast compared with those of most other frogs, so breeding can be completed before the pond dries up.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-200</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-200">#cite_note-200</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>200</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Some frog species are adapted to a cold environment. The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wood_frog">/wiki/Wood_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Wood frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>wood frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Rana sylvatica</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>), whose habitat extends into the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arctic_Circle">/wiki/Arctic_Circle</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Arctic Circle</a>"&gt;</span><span>Arctic Circle</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, buries itself in the ground during winter. Although much of its body freezes during this time, it maintains a high concentration of glucose in its vital organs, which protects them from damage.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Exploratorium_54-5</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-Exploratorium-54">#cite_note-Exploratorium-54</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>54</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>

</span></span><span id="line2813"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>In 2006, of 4,035 species of amphibians that depend on water during some lifecycle stage, 1,356 (33.6%) were considered to be threatened. This is likely to be an underestimate because it excludes 1,427 species for which evidence was insufficient to assess their status.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-201</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-201">#cite_note-201</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>201</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Frog populations have declined dramatically since the 1950s. More than one-third of frog species are considered to be threatened with </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Extinction">/wiki/Extinction</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Extinction</a>"&gt;</span><span>extinction</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, and more than 120 species are believed to have become extinct since the 1980s.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Stuart_202-0</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-Stuart-202">#cite_note-Stuart-202</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span </span></span><span id="line2817"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog_mutations_and_genetic_defects">/wiki/Frog_mutations_and_genetic_defects</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Frog mutations and genetic defects</a>"&gt;</span><span>Frog mutations and genetic defects</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> have increased since the 1990s. These often include missing legs or extra legs. Various causes have been identified or hypothesized, including an increase in </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ultraviolet">/wiki/Ultraviolet</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ultraviolet</a>"&gt;</span><span>ultraviolet radiation</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> affecting the spawn on the surface of ponds, chemical contamination from pesticides and fertilizers, and parasites such as the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trematode">/wiki/Trematode</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Trematode</a>"&gt;</span><span>trematode</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ribeiroia_ondatrae">/wiki/Ribeiroia_ondatrae</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ribeiroia ondatrae</a>"&gt;</span><span>Ribeiroia ondatrae</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>. Probably all these are involved in a complex way as </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stressor">/wiki/Stressor</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Stressor</a>"&gt;</span><span>stressors</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, environmental factors contributing to rates of disease, and vulnerability to attack by parasites. Malformations impair mobility and the individuals may not survive to adulthood. An increase in the number of frogs eaten by birds may actually increase the likelihood of parasitism of other frogs, because the trematode's complex lifecycle includes the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Planorbidae">/wiki/Planorbidae</a>" <span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/World_Association_of_Zoos_and_Aquariums">/wiki/World_Association_of_Zoos_and_Aquariums</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">World Association of Zoos and Aquariums</a>"&gt;</span><span>World Association of Zoos and Aquariums</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> named 2008 as the "Year of the Frog" in order to draw attention to the conservation issues faced by them.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-214</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-214">#cite_note-214</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>214</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2819"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cane_toad">/wiki/Cane_toad</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Cane toad</a>"&gt;</span><span>cane toad</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Rhinella marina</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) is a very adaptable species native to South and Central America. In the 1930s, it was introduced into Puerto Rico, and later various other islands in the Pacific and Caribbean region, as a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biological_pest_control">/wiki/Biological_pest_control</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Biological pest control</a>"&gt;</span><span>biological pest control</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> agent.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-215</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-215">#cite_note-215</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>215</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> In 1935, 3000 toads were liberated in the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sugar_cane">/wiki/Sugar_cane</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Sugar cane</a>"&gt;</span><span>sugar cane</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> fields of Queensland, Australia, in an attempt to control </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cane_beetle">/wiki/Cane_beetle</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Cane beetle</a>"&gt;</span><span>cane beetles</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> such as </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Dermolepida albohirtum</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>, the larvae of which damage and kill the canes. Initial results in many of these countries were positive, but it later became apparent that the toads upset the ecological balance in their new environments. They bred freely, competed with native frog species, ate bees and other harmless native invertebrates, had few predators in their adopted habitats, and poisoned pets, carnivorous birds, and mammals. In many of these countries, they are now regarded both as pests and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Invasive_species">/wiki/Invasive_species</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Invasive species</a>"&gt;</span><span>invasive species</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, and scientists are looking for a biological method to control them.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-216</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-216">#cite_note-216</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>216</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2820"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2821"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">div</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-heading mw-heading2</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">h2</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Human_uses</a>"&gt;</span><span>Human uses</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">h2</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">div</span>&gt;</span><span>

</span></span><span id="line2831"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">figure</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-default-size</a>" <span class="attribute-name">typeof</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw:File/Thumb</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:2012_Froschschenkel_anagoria.JPG">/wiki/File:2012_Froschschenkel_anagoria.JPG</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-file-description</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">img</span> <span class="attribute-name">src</span>="<a class="end-tag">figure</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2832"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog_legs">/wiki/Frog_legs</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Frog legs</a>"&gt;</span><span>Frog legs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> are eaten by humans in many parts of the world. Indonesia is the world's largest exporter of frog meat, exporting more than 5,000 tonnes of frog meat each year, mostly to France, Belgium and Luxembourg.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-abc_news_217-0</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-abc_news-217">#cite_note-abc_news-217</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>217</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Originally, they were supplied from local wild populations, but overexploitation led to a diminution in the supply. This resulted in the development of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aquaculture">/wiki/Aquaculture</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Aquaculture</a>"&gt;</span><span>frog farming</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and a global trade in frogs. The main importing countries are France, Belgium, Luxembourg, and the United States, while the chief exporting nations are Indonesia and China.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-Warkentin_218-0</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" King</a>"&gt;</span><span>Thomas J. King</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> cloned a frog by </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Somatic_cell_nuclear_transfer">/wiki/Somatic_cell_nuclear_transfer</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Somatic cell nuclear transfer</a>"&gt;</span><span>somatic cell nuclear transfer</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. This same technique was later used to create </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dolly_(sheep)">/wiki/Dolly_(sheep)</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Dolly (sheep)</a>"&gt;</span><span>Dolly the sheep</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, and their experiment was the first time a successful nuclear transplantation had been accomplished in higher animals.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-226</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-226">#cite_note-226</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>226</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2840"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Frogs are used in cloning research and other branches of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Embryology">/wiki/Embryology</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Embryology</a>"&gt;</span><span>embryology</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>.  Although alternative pregnancy tests have been developed, biologists continue to use </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Xenopus</span><span>&lt;/<span </span></span><span id="line2845"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Because frog toxins are extraordinarily diverse, they have raised the interest of biochemists as a "natural pharmacy". The alkaloid </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epibatidine">/wiki/Epibatidine</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Epibatidine</a>"&gt;</span><span>epibatidine</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, a painkiller 200 times more potent than </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Morphine">/wiki/Morphine</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Morphine</a>"&gt;</span><span>morphine</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, is made by some species of </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Poison_dart_frog">/wiki/Poison_dart_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Poison dart frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>poison dart frogs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. </span></span><span id="line2846"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>It has long been suspected that pre-Columbian </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mesoamerica">/wiki/Mesoamerica</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Mesoamerica</a>"&gt;</span><span>Mesoamericans</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> used a toxic secretion produced by the cane toad as a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hallucinogen">/wiki/Hallucinogen</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Hallucinogen</a>"&gt;</span><span>hallucinogen</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, but more likely they used substances secreted by the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorado_River_toad">/wiki/Colorado_River_toad</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Colorado River toad</a>"&gt;</span><span>Colorado River toad</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Bufo alvarius</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>). These contain </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bufotenin">/wiki/Bufotenin</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bufotenin</a>"&gt;</span><span>bufotenin</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (5-MeO-DMT), a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychoactive_drug">/wiki/Psychoactive_drug</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Psychoactive drug</a>"&gt;</span><span>psychoactive compound</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> that has been used in modern times as a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Recreational_drug">/wiki/Recreational_drug</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Recreational drug</a>"&gt;</span><span>recreational drug</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. Typically, the skin secretions are dried and then smoked.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-232</a>" <span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span> Illicit drug use by licking the skin of a toad has been reported in the media, but this may be an </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>233</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2847"><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Exudations from the skin of the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Golden_poison_frog">/wiki/Golden_poison_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Golden poison frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>golden poison frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Phyllobates terribilis</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) are traditionally used by native Colombians to poison the darts they use for hunting. The tip of the projectile is rubbed over the back of the frog and the dart is launched from a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Blowgun">/wiki/Blowgun</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Blowgun</a>"&gt;</span><span>blowgun</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. The combination of the two alkaloid toxins </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Batrachotoxin">/wiki/Batrachotoxin</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Batrachotoxin</a>"&gt;</span><span>batrachotoxin</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Homobatrachotoxin">/wiki/Homobatrachotoxin</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Homobatrachotoxin</a>"&gt;</span><span>homobatrachotoxin</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> is so powerful, one frog contains enough poison to kill an estimated 22,000 mice.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-dartpoison_234-0</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>234</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kokoe_poison_dart_frog">/wiki/Kokoe_poison_dart_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Kokoe poison dart frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>Kokoe poison dart frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Phyllobates aurotaenia</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) and the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black-legged_dart_frog">/wiki/Black-legged_dart_frog</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Black-legged dart frog</a>"&gt;</span><span>black-legged dart frog</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> (</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>Phyllobates bicolor</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">i</span>&gt;</span><span>) are also used for this purpose. These are less toxic and less abundant than the golden poison frog. They are impaled on pointed sticks and may be heated over a fire to maximise the quantity of poison that can be transferred to the dart.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite_ref-dartpoison_234-1</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">reference</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-dartpoison-234">#cite_note-dartpoison-234</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#91;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span>234</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">cite-bracket</a>"&gt;</span><span><span class="entity"><span>&amp;</span>#93;</span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">span</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">sup</span>&gt;</span><span>

</span></span><span id="line2850"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">div</span> <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-heading mw-heading3</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">h3</span> <span class="attribute-name">id</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Cultural_significance</a>"&gt;</span><span>Cultural significance</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">h3</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">div</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2851"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">link</span> <span class="attribute-name">rel</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-deduplicated-inline-style</a>" <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1236090951">mw-data:TemplateStyles:r1236090951</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">div</span> <span class="attribute-name">role</span>="<a class="attribute-value">note</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">hatnote navigation-not-searchable</a>"&gt;</span><span>Main article: </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frogs_in_culture">/wiki/Frogs_in_culture</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Frogs in culture</a>"&gt;</span><span>Frogs in culture</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">div</span>&gt;</span><span>
</span></span><span id="line2852"><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">p</span>&gt;</span><span>Frogs have been featured in mythology, </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fairy_tale">/wiki/Fairy_tale</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Fairy tale</a>"&gt;</span><span>fairy tales</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> and popular culture. In traditional Chinese myths, the world rests on a giant frog, who would try to swallow the moon, causing the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lunar_eclipse">/wiki/Lunar_eclipse</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Lunar eclipse</a>"&gt;</span><span>lunar eclipse</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. Frogs have been featured in religion, folklore, and popular culture. The </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ancient_Egyptian">/wiki/Ancient_Egyptian</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Ancient Egyptian</a>"&gt;</span><span>ancient Egyptians</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> depicted the god </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Heqet">/wiki/Heqet</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Heqet</a>"&gt;</span><span>Heqet</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, protector of newborns, with the head of a frog. For the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mayan_civilization">/wiki/Mayan_civilization</a>" <span class="attribute-name">class</span>="<a class="attribute-value">mw-redirect</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Mayan civilization</a>"&gt;</span><span>Mayans</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, frogs represented water, crops, fertility and birth and were associated with the god </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chaac">/wiki/Chaac</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Chaac</a>"&gt;</span><span>Chaac</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>. In the </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bible">/wiki/Bible</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Bible</a>"&gt;</span><span>Bible</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>, </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Moses">/wiki/Moses</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Moses</a>"&gt;</span><span>Moses</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> unleashes a </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Plagues_of_Egypt">/wiki/Plagues_of_Egypt</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Plagues of Egypt</a>"&gt;</span><span>plague of frogs</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span> on the Egyptians. Medieval Europeans associated frogs and toads with evil and </span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">a</span> <span class="attribute-name">href</span>="<a class="attribute-value" href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Witchcraft">/wiki/Witchcraft</a>" <span class="attribute-name">title</span>="<a class="attribute-value">Witchcraft</a>"&gt;</span><span>witchcraft</span><span>&lt;/<span class="end-tag">a</span>&gt;</span><span>.</span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">sup</span> <span href="view-source:https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Frog#cite_note-culture-235">#cite_note-culture-235</a>"&gt;</span><span></span><span>&lt;<span class="start-tag">span</span> <span
